    "content": "<div class=\"noinclude\"><span class=\"breadcrumbs xulRefAttr_breadcrumbs\">Â« <a href=\"/en-US/docs/XUL/XUL_Reference\">XUL Reference home</a></span></div>\n\n<dl>\n <dt><code id=\"a-menuitem.type\"><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Tech/XUL/Attribute/menuitem.type\">type</a></code></dt>\n <dd>Type: <em>one of the values below</em></dd>\n <dd>Can be used to create checkable menuitems or for radio button menuitems.</dd>\n <dd>\n <dl>\n  <dt><code>checkbox</code></dt>\n  <dd>The <code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Tech/XUL/menuitem\" title=\"menuitem\">menuitem</a></code> is checked. The <code id=\"a-checked\"><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Tech/XUL/Attribute/checked\">checked</a></code> attribute determines whether the menuitem is checked or not.</dd>\n  <dt><code>radio</code></dt>\n  <dd>The <code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Tech/XUL/menuitem\" title=\"menuitem\">menuitem</a></code> becomes part of a radio group. Other menuitems that have the same value for their <code id=\"a-name\"><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Tech/XUL/Attribute/name\">name</a></code> attributes are part of the same <code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Tech/XUL/radio\" title=\"radio\">radio</a></code> group. Only one menuitem in the same radio group can be checked at once.</dd>\n </dl>\n </dd>\n</dl>\n\n<p>More information on adding checkmarks to menus in the <a href=\"/en/XUL_Tutorial/More_Menu_Features#Adding_Checkmarks_to_Menus\" title=\"en/XUL_Tutorial/More_Menu_Features#Adding_Checkmarks_to_Menus\">XUL tutorial</a></p>",
